  <subsection>
    <title>Activities</title>
  <activity xml:id="quadratic-inequality-coeff-greater-than">
    <introduction>
      <p>Recall that when solving a quadratic equation, you can first try to factor the quadratic. Solving inequalities will require multiple steps. Solve the quadratic inequality <m>x^2-4x \gt 32</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> First, move all terms to one side. Then factor the quadratic function, <m>f(x)=x^2-4x-32</m>.
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>(x-4)(x+8)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(x-8)(x+4)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(x-8)(x-4)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(x+8)(x+4)</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
    <task>
        <p> Now set each factor <m>=0</m> and solve for <m>x</m>. These are the <m>x</m> intercepts.   
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>-8</m>, <m>-4</m></p></li>
          <li><p> <m>8</m>, <m>4</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>-8</m>, <m>4</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>8</m>, <m>-4</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> Create a number line and place the values from each factor on this number line. We will now test all <m>3</m> intervals between the <m>2</m> values to see if we get positive or a negative result. Record these signs in the intervals and shade the desired result. This is called a sign chart. We want only the intervals that are <m> \gt 0</m>, i.e. positive.
      <ol marker="A." cols="1">
        <li><p> <m>x \gt 8</m>,<m>x \lt -4</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>x \gt -8</m>,<m>x \gt -4</m></p></li>
        <li><p> <m>x \lt 8</m>,<m>x \lt 4</m> </p></li>
        <li><p> <m>x \lt -8</m>,<m>x \gt 4</m> </p></li>
        
    </ol> </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p> Write the intervals using interval notation.
    <ol marker="A." cols="1">
      <li><p><m>(-8,4)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(4,8)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(-\infty,-4)\cup(8,\infty)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(-\infty,-8)\cup(4,\infty)</m> </p></li>
      
  </ol> </p>
</task>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="quadratic-inequality-coeff-less-than-0">
    <introduction>
      <p>Solve the quadratic inequality <m>5x^2+63 \lt 52x</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    \<task>
      <p> Follow the steps above and write your answer in interval notation.
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>\left(-9,-\frac{7}{5}\right)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-\infty,\frac{7}{5})U(9,\infty)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-\frac{7}{5},9)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(\frac{7}{5},9)</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="quadratic-inequality-coeff-greater-than-or-equal-0">
    <introduction>
      <p>Solve the quadratic inequality <m>-2x^2-10x-10 \ge 6x+20</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    \<task>
      <p> Follow the steps above and write your answer in interval notation.
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>[-5,-3]</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-infinity,-5]U[-3,infinity)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>[3,5]</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-infinity,3]U[5,infinity)</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
    \<task>
      <p> How can we confirm visually that our solution is correct?
         </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="rational-inequality-greater-than-0">
    <introduction>
      <p>Solve the rational inequality <me>\frac{5x-3}{x+4} \gt 7</me>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> First, move all terms to one side. Then find the common denominator and combine to one simplified fraction. 
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>\frac{12x+31}{x+4}</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>\frac{12x-31}{x+4}</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>\frac{-2x+31}{x+4}</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>\frac{-2x-31}{x+4}</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
    <task>
        <p> Now set each factor in the numerator and denominator <m>=0</m> and solve for <m>x</m>. These are the partition values to place on the number line for testing intervals.   
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>-\frac{31}{2},-4</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>\frac{31}{2},-4</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>\frac{31}{12},-4</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>-\frac{31}{12},-4</m> </p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> Create a number line and place the values from each factor on this number line. We will now test all intervals between the <m>2</m> values to see if we get a positive or a negative result. Record these signs in the intervals and shade the desired result. This is called a sign chart. We want only the intervals that are <m> \gt 0</m>, i.e. positive.
      <ol marker="A." cols="1">
        <li><p> <m>x \gt -\frac{31}{2}</m>,<m>x \lt -4</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>x \gt \frac{31}{2}</m>,<m>x \lt -4</m></p></li>
        <li><p> <m>x \gt -\frac{31}{2}</m>,<m>x \lt 4</m> </p></li>
        <li><p> <m>x \lt \frac{31}{2}</m>,<m>x \gt 4</m> </p></li>
        
    </ol> </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p> Write the intervals using interval notation.
    <ol marker="A." cols="1">
      <li><p><m>(-\frac{31}{2},4)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(4,8)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(-infinity,-4)U(8,infinity)</m></p></li>
      <li><p> <m>(-infinity,-8)U(4,infinity)</m> </p></li>
      
  </ol> </p>
</task>
    \<task>
      <p> How can we confirm visually that our solution is correct?
         </p>
    </task>
  </activity>

  <activity xml:id="rational-inequality-both-sides">
    <introduction>
      <p>Solve the rational inequality <me>\frac{8x+16}{x-2} \lt \frac{x+10}{x+5}</me>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> Write answer using interval notation. 
        <ol marker="A." cols="1">
          <li><p><m>(-infinity, -5)U(2,infinity)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-5,-\frac{6}{7})U(-\frac{6}{7},2)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-\frac{6}{7},2)</m> </p></li>
          <li><p> <m>(-5,-\frac{6}{7})</m></p></li>
      </ol> </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  
